Eyimofe and Nwakaego Boyo are a super celebrity couple who love to live their lives moderately. Of course, Omamofe, the husband is a billionaire oil mogul, while the wife, Nwakaego, a Nollywood sweetheart known as Ego Boyo. Yet, this fantastic couple maintains a dignifying lifestyle devoid of the boisterous one associated with their famous peers. However, anytime the Boyos have any reason to celebrate, they ensure it’s a major blowout like they did penultimate Saturday when their son, Eyisan took his heartthrob, Keji Maryam Belgore to the altar. Ilorin, Kwara State came alive as some of the crème of Nigerian social establishment stormed the town for the first leg of the line-up of wedding ceremonies with the traditional wedding/Nikkai ceremony of Keji, the daughter of Justice Alfa Belgore, a former Chief Justice of Nigeria and the love of her life, Eyisan. While the Belgores are known for hosting big parties with their influential guests, Mofe Boyo, the deputy Group Chief Executive, Oando Plc, alongside Ego, his beautiful wife had their own around for the wedding and played perfect hosts to their powerful guests which included the Speaker of the House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila; Wife of the Vice President, Dolapo Osinbajo; Toyin Saraki, wife of former Senate President, Dr. Bukola Saraki; Amb. Folake AbdulRasaq, wife of Kwara Governor; Iyalode Bintu Tinubu; President of the Nigerian Bar Association (NBA), Mr. Olumide Akpata, billionaire mogul, Hajia Bola Shagaya, Richard Mofe-Damijo, Joke Silva, Kate Henshaw, Rita Dominic, Mildred Okwo, among several others.